title: Westbrook leads Thunder to 113-102 victory over Jazz
text:
Home » News » Sports » NBA » Westbrook leads Thunder to… Westbrook leads Thunder to 113-102 victory over Jazz By KAREEM COPELAND October 20, 2015 11:32 pm Utah Jazz guard Raul Neto (25) drives around Oklahoma City Thunder guard Cameron Payne (22) during the second quarter of an NBA preseason basketball game Tuesday, Oct. 20, 2015, in Salt Lake City. (AP Photo/Rick Bowmer) 
SALT LAKE CITY (AP) — Russell Westbrook scored 21 points as the Oklahoma City Thunder closed out their preseason with a 113-102 win over the Utah Jazz. The four-time All-Star had a triple-double with 10 rebounds and 10 assists. 
Rodney Hood led the Jazz with 23 off the bench. 
THUNDER: Serge Ibaka scored 16 on 7 for 14 shooting. … Steven Adams finished with 14 points and 10 rebounds. 
JAZZ: Rudy Gobert stuggled throughout with five points, four rebounds and two blocks. He had a minus-23 plus-minus in the first half. … Trey Burke put up 20 points despite a horrid first half. … Gordon Hayward scored 18 points. 
STAR WATCH: Kevin Durant looked to be in midseason form. Durant scored 11 in the first quarter on 4 for 6 shooting from the field. He finished with 29. 
UP NEXT: The Jazz host the Nuggets for their final preseason game on Thursday. The Thunder host the Spurs in their regular season opener Nov. 28. Topics:
